clinical_particulars.therapeutic_indications: For use as an inhalation agent for induction and or maintenance of anesthesia for inpatient and outpatient surgery in adults

contraindications.pharmacodynamics: Desflurane is a general inhalation anesthetic It induces muscle relaxation and reduces pains sensitivity by altering tissue excitability It does so by decreasing the extent of gap junction mediated cell cell coupling and altering the activity of the channels that underlie the action potential
